original: Ehrnström, Gustaf Einar Andreas, kyrkoherde, Björköby, f. 31/1/92 i Ma-desjö, Kalm. 1, av folkskoLl. o. kant. Johannes E. o. Hulda Petersson. G. 24 m. Edith Carlsson. Barn: Gunnel f. 25, Eva 26, Gunnar 28, Anita 29, Edith 31, Nils-Magnus 33, Harald 36. — Stud:ex. i Kalm. 11, teol. kand., prakt. teol. prov samt prästv. f. Växjö stift 15. Varit v. pastor i Ås, Vent-linge, Resmo, Traryd, Björkö o. Karlstorp, v. kommin. i Mörbylånga, Våt-huit o. Kr åks hult ’samt kommin. i Nä-velsjö, kyrkoh. i Björkö sed. 35. Ordf. i kyrkofullm., past:stämma o. skol&tyr.
translated: Ehrnström, Gustaf Einar Andreas, pastor, Björköby, born on January 31, 1892 in Madesjö, Kalmar County, son of elementary school teacher and cantor Johannes E. and Hulda Petersson. Married to Edith Carlsson in 1924. Children: Gunnel born in 1925, Eva in 1926, Gunnar in 1928, Anita in 1929, Edith in 1931, Nils-Magnus in 1933, Harald in 1936. He passed his high school exam in Kalmar in 1911, earned a Bachelor of Theology degree, passed practical theology exams, and was ordained as a priest for Växjö diocese in 1915. He has served as a deputy pastor in Ås, Ventlinge, Resmo, Traryd, Björkö, and Karlstorp, and as a second pastor in Mörbylånga, Våthult and Kråkshult, as well as a pastor in Nävelsjö and the vicar in Björkö since 1935. He has been chairman of the church board, the clergy assembly, and the school board.
